Description: Body sherd of Corinthian pottery globular aryballos; exterior: painted decoration consisting of part of elaborate quatrefoil pattern with added red.

Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 54, no. A12)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 217, no. 3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.127) (Phase 1)
